OL,6,FSentencing, Judge Goddard told Baros:
OL,7,F"In my judgement you do not present a
OL,8,Frisk or danger to the public. You have
OL,9,Fa good record, an absence of previous
OL,10,Fconvictions and you have shown remorse.
OL,12,F"Here there is a realistic prospect of
OL,13,Frehabilitation, strong personal
OL,14,Fmitigation, and immediate custody will
OL,15,Fresult in significant harmful impact
OL,16,Fupon others."
OL,18,FBaros, of Bentinck Street, Ashton-
OL,19,Funder-Lyne, was sentenced to 20 months
OL,20,Fin prison, suspended for two years.
